## ⚠️ The Golden Rules of Bash `if`

> [!CAUTION]
> ### Rule #1: Spaces are MANDATORY!
> In Bash, `[` and `[[` are actual **commands**, not just syntax characters. Therefore, you must separate them with spaces.
> * ❌ **Wrong:** `if ["$var"=="test"]`
> * **Right:** `if [ "$var" == "test" ]`

> [!IMPORTANT]
> ### Rule #2: Always Quote Your Variables!
> Always wrap your variables in double quotes (`"$my_var"`). If the variable is empty or contains spaces, omitting quotes will cause the script to crash with a `syntax error`.

